quran[35]{c,v,t}:
  70,1,A challenger has demanded a punishment bound to come
  70,2,for the disbelievers—to be averted by none—
  70,3,"from God, Lord of pathways of ˹heavenly˺ ascent"
  70,4,˹through which˺ the angels and the ˹holy˺ spirit will ascend to Him on a Day fifty thousand years in length
  70,5,"So endure ˹this denial, O Prophet,˺ with beautiful patience"
  70,6,They truly see this ˹Day˺ as impossible
  70,7,but We see it as inevitable
  70,8,On that Day the sky will be like molten brass
  70,9,and the mountains like ˹tufts of˺ wool
  70,10,And no close friend will ask ˹about˺ their friends
  70,11,˹although˺ they will be made to see each other. The wicked will wish to ransom themselves from the punishment of that Day by their children
  70,12,"their spouses, their siblings"
  70,13,their clan that sheltered them
  70,14,"and everyone on earth altogether, just to save themselves"
  70,15,But no! There will certainly be a raging Flame
  70,16,ripping off scalps
  70,17,It will summon whoever turned their backs ˹on God˺ and turned away ˹from the truth˺
  70,18,and gathered and hoarded ˹wealth˺
  70,19,"Indeed, humankind was created impatient"
  70,20,distressed when touched with evil
  70,21,and withholding when touched with good—
  70,22,except those who pray
  70,23,consistently performing their prayers
  70,24,and who give the rightful share of their wealth
  70,25,to the beggar and the poor
  70,26,and who ˹firmly˺ believe in the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and those who fear the punishment of their Lord—
  70,28,˹knowing that˺ none should feel secure from their Lord’s punishment—
  70,29,and those who guard their chastity
  70,30,"except with their wives or those ˹bondwomen˺ in their possession, for then they are free from blame"
  70,31,but whoever seeks beyond that are the transgressors
  70,32,˹The faithful are˺ also those who are true to their trusts and covenants
  70,33,and who are honest in their testimony
  70,34,and who are ˹properly˺ observant of their prayers
  70,35,"These will be in Gardens, held in honour"